<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1187&amp;p=6217#p6217"><![CDATA[
Classic Shell ships with a Windows File Explorer toolbar which puts back important functions. Due to a bug in Explorer, sometimes it gets confused between toolbars, especially when one of the toolbars is uninstalled. Therefore it is recommended before uninstall that you hide Classic Shell's toolbar. On Windows 7, this can be done by right clicking the Explorer <strong>menu bar</strong> and unchecking &quot;Classic Explorer Bar&quot;. On Windows 8, to hide the Classic Explorer toolbar, go to the View tab of the Ribbon, click the Options dropdown menu button (note, not the Options button itself, buts the little black arrow below it) and uncheck Classic Explorer Bar.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Thu Aug 29, 2013 8:27 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
