First time here and I just want to say many thanks and appreciations for your Classic Shell software which I just installed it today. No more shall I have to suffer through the no Start Button which listed all my programs or that stupid Metro screen. I have been a MS Windows fan since Windows 95 up until this atrocious Windows 8. You guys save me from abandon Windows and looking toward to Apple OS. Again, thanks guys! I just wish I encounter this program/forum sooner.<br /><br />One question I have while reading the FAQ tab, I was kind of confuse when I got to the uninstall part:<br />[<strong>What is the right way to uninstall Classic Shell?</strong><br />To uninstall Classic Shell follow these steps:<br />3. Make sure the toolbar is hidden (if you uninstall while the toolbar is visible, the menu bar in Explorer will get stuck in the visible state and you won’t be able to hide it) <strong><br /><br />After I uninstalled Classic Shell I can't hide the menu in Explorer any more. What do I do?<br /></strong>If you missed step 3 from the uninstall instructions and you are having problems with the menu, you have two options:<br />Go to the registry, open the <strong>HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Internet Explorer\Toolbar\ShellBrowser</strong> key and delete the <strong>ITBar7Layout</strong> value]<br /><br />My question is what does &quot;toolbar is hidden&quot; refer to in window explorer? Is it from the Folder Option which one has to put a check mark under Don't show hidden<br />file/ folder/driver or something else?<br /><br />Other than the above, I'm all good. Got a chance to play around with Classic shell Button and change it to a different logo. Next step is to search the forum for changing the color of the taskbar.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1481">REMINATOR</a> — Thu Aug 29, 2013 8:12 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
